headline: Warning: Don't Buy Just Any High-Yielding Dividend Stock for Passive Income. Focus on This Key Characteristic.
summary: Buying dividend stocks can be a terrific way to generate passive income.  Many companies consistently pay quarterly dividends (and some even pay monthly), allowing you to collect recurring cash flow to cover your living expenses or reinvest into more dividend stocks to grow your passive income.  As your passive income grows, you'll become more financially independent.
